Andropogoneae Species

Michelle C. Stitzer

2024-12-19

Zea luxurians

Assembly is haploid, and the genome is paleotetraploid. It has a haploid genome size of 3100 Mb, and has 10 haploid chromosomes.

Species herbarium records

Herbarium records of Zea luxurians from AuBuchon-Elder et al 2022 are plotted with black points, The sampled individual this genome was generated from is shown in a colored point. The green background shows the biogeographic ranges of all Andropogoneae species in AuBuchon-Elder et al 2022.

Highlighted Figure 1

Figure 1 from the main text, with Zea luxurians highlighted with colored points.

Highlighted Figure 2

Figure 2 from the main text, with Zea luxurians highlighted with colored points.

Dotplot of Zea luxurians vs. Paspalum vaginatum.

Like dotplots shown in Figure 3 of the main text, this shows syntenic blocks in Zea luxurians along the y-axis, vs P. vaginatum on the x-axis. As Zea luxurians is a paleotetraploid with a haploid, assembly, we expect 2 paths for any x-axis position.

Fractionation of Zea luxurians

Like plots shown in Figure 4 of the main text, this shows proportion of retained genes in Zea luxurians along the y-axis, vs P. vaginatum chromosomes on the x-axis. As Zea luxurians is a paleotetraploid with a haploid, assembly, we expect 2 lines, one for each subgenome.
